<ul>
  <li>
    <p><strong>Make them feel good about themselves.</strong> Validate their positive attributes which they think they possess</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Tell an insecure person that theyâ€™re good or important and youâ€™ll get persecuted or ignored. But as every dictator and demagogue in history has relied upon as a law, tell the right man that heâ€™s brilliant and heâ€™ll put a crown on your head.  Iâ€™ve never met a conman who didnâ€™t open with some variant â€œwell you look like a bright young fellowâ€. It doesnâ€™t work on everyone, but it does work on those susceptible to it with astounding success rates. Trumpâ€™s CPAC speech is such a good example. Itâ€™s also a good example of the sort of tactics employed by Pick Up Artists - the negging, the disorientation, followed by the â€˜but youâ€™re so smart that you agree with everything I say.</li>
    </ul>
